{"id":34937,"date":"2021-01-15T11:50:36","date_gmt":"2021-01-15T07:50:36","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=34937"},"modified":"2021-04-06T15:40:50","modified_gmt":"2021-04-06T11:40:50","slug":"munkar-nakir-questions","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/15\/munkar-nakir-questions\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Death: Munkar and Nakir questions souls in the grave"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>When the deceased is buried in his grave, two black and blue angels come to him. One of them is called Munkar and the other is called Nakir. They will both say: What do you say about this man? He will say what he said before: He is the servant of Allah and His messenger, I bear witness there is no God but Allah and Muhammad is His servant and His messenger. They will both say: We knew you would say this! Then his grave is expanded by seventy cubits on each side, it is illuminated for him, and it is said to him: Sleep! He will say: May I return to my family to tell them? They will both say: Sleep like a bridegroom, whom none awakens but the most beloved of his family, until Allah resurrects him from his place of rest. If he was a hypocrite, he will say to the angels: I heard people saying something, so I said the same as them, for I do not know! They will both say: We knew you would say that! It will be said to the earth to constrict him, so it will constrict him by squeezing his ribs together. He will continue being punished until Allah resurrects him from that place of his.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 1071<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Jayyid<\/em> (very good) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644